  "text": "Descriptor hyper-parameters. The structural descriptors CM, ACSF, MBTR and SOAP have method-specific parameters which can be fitted to the investigated system. A few performance tests showed that the mean absolute error (MAE) was sensitive to a few of those hyper-parameters. The radial cutoff of the local CM was optimised to 6 Å. The rows and columns of the matrix were sorted with respect to the L2-norm. Regarding ACSF, only the radial cutoff R c was optimised. For other parameters, all combinations of sensible values inspired by Behler, [CITATION_1] were used to construct symmetry functions. Table 1 shows the values used for the parameters ζ, κ, η, λ and R s , which in combination formed symmetry functions from Supplementary Eqs. (S2)-(S5). ACSF H denotes the symmetry functions with hydrogen as the center atom.",
